  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/1532",
  "title": "connectCurrentRefinements API",
  "body": "This connector is used to be able to display the current refinements, and also to be able to clear them (one by one or every refinements).\r\n\r\nTo do that, the user has access to a prop called items, which follow this structure: `array.<{clear: function, label: string}>. The label follow the format 'facetName: facetValue'.`\r\n\r\nSo let's say we have a refinementList with three colors checked, you will have something like:\r\n`[{\"label\":\"colors: Black\"},{\"label\":\"colors: White\"},{\"label\":\"colors: Black-brown\"}]` (stringify version, each object has also the clear function). \r\n\r\nThe format 'facetName: facetValue' corresponds to the one declared in the refinementList metadata. \r\n\r\nWhile it's fine if the CurrentRefinements widget display the label directly this way (if we think it's the best way to display them), I think that for the connector, it's maybe not the easiest structure to manipulate. What I suggest, is that we don't provide a label and instead have a new key `values` with a structure like:  \r\n\r\n`array.<{clear: function, values: array.<facetName: string, facetValues: array<string>}>.`\r\n\r\nAlso, the clear function is used internally by the refine function of the connector. If the user look at the item structure it may be confused and try to use that instead of the refine function to clear the refinements. Maybe we could rename it to '_clear', to make it clear that it's private? \r\n\r\nWhat do you think? ",
